                                Blanker

        Blanker causes the screen to go blank when there has been no
activity for more than a certain amount of time (the default is 60
seconds). This saves your monitor from screen burn. If you don't use the
mouse or press a key on the keyboard for 60 seconds the screen will blank
out until you do. Double-click on the Blanker icon and a window appears
requesting the amount of time that you wish to elapse before the screen
goes blank. Either use the new value. To get rid of the window click on the
close gadget or the Hide gadget. To exit the Blanker altogether, double
click on the Blanker icon and click on Quit. There is a Project menu which
duplicates the Hide and Quit options, with keyboard equivalents Right
Amiga-H and Right Amiga-Q. You can also use Tool Types to set the time to
elapse before the screen goes blank. Consult your Workbench manual for more
details.

      Workbench 3 has two more options enable you to cycle colours when the
screen goes blank or display a random spline animation.


